Hey guys! It’s me. Grateful to have some new friends following along with me recently (thanks for being here, both old and new friends)...soooo I thought I’d do a little introduction ♡ <<• Plus I just really love this self-portrait of me in all my favorite White Buffalo jewels...and these glasses are an absolute vibe. Gotta give this one a permanent spot on the feed •>>

I’m Heather. I’m 34 years young living in southwest Colorado with my fiancé @tburgewood and our 3 fur children 🐈🐕🐈

I love to create and work with my hands. I’ve been silversmithing for almost 6 years and even did it full time for awhile until an opportunity to work at my buddy’s shop presented itself.

I treasure my family and friends. I turn to nature for guidance often. I love to start each day with a cup of coffee and a walk with my pup in the woods. And end each day with a hot cup of tea and a soak in my tub.

I’ve lived in that one-day-at-a-time state of mind many times in my life. And I’m not one bit ashamed. I’m more aware, grateful and present because of tough and challenging experiences. For these places and times are from where growth springs.

My favorite artist is Vincent van Gogh and has been since I was in 2nd grade. My favorite book is The Celestine Prophecy— it’s where my absolute trust + belief in synchronicity comes from. My favorite food is any meal shared at home with loved ones. And my current favorite brewery/seltzery is @untitledartbev

I’m a firm believer in the notion that the only constant in life is change. It keeps me on my toes and adaptable and excited for what’s next.

Writing about oneself is hard! That’s all I got for now. If you read all that..thanks for showing interest in me as a person as well as my art/jewelry.

Happy long weekend, everyone ♡ Stay well & be safe!

